      • getOnDuplicate

        public ImportOptions.OnDuplicate getOnDuplicate()
        (optional) Controls what action is carried out in case of a unique key constraint violation. Possible values are: OnDuplicate.ERROR: this will not import the current document because of the unique key constraint violation. This is the default setting. OnDuplicate.UPDATE: this will update an existing document in the database with the data specified in the request. Attributes of the existing document that are not present in the request will be preseved. OnDuplicate.REPLACE: this will replace an existing document in the database with the data specified in the request. OnDuplicate.IGNORE: this will not update an existing document and simply ignore the error caused by the unique key constraint violation.
        Returns:

      • setOnDuplicate

        public ImportOptions setOnDuplicate(ImportOptions.OnDuplicate onDuplicate)
        (optional) Controls what action is carried out in case of a unique key constraint violation. Possible values are: OnDuplicate.ERROR: this will not import the current document because of the unique key constraint violation. This is the default setting. OnDuplicate.UPDATE: this will update an existing document in the database with the data specified in the request. Attributes of the existing document that are not present in the request will be preseved. OnDuplicate.REPLACE: this will replace an existing document in the database with the data specified in the request. OnDuplicate.IGNORE: this will not update an existing document and simply ignore the error caused by the unique key constraint violation.
